Tragedy struck in Bauchi State as a young man, known as Abdulrahman Sulaiman allegedly killed his elder brother following a minor misunderstanding between them. It was learned that the 18-year-old Abdulrahman Sulaiman, who resides around Games Village area of Bauchi metropolis, allegedly stabbed his elder brother for taking his shorts and wearing them, a development which annoyed him. According to neighbours, the deceased was stabbed to death as a result of a misunderstanding that ensued between the brothers. They said that all efforts by both parents and others to pacify the enraged young man proved difficult as he refused to be pacified but rather took a sharp knife and stabbed his unsuspecting elder brother. The elder brother was rushed to the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa University Teaching Hospital (ATBUTH), Bauchi where he was confirmed dead after losing so much blood from the spot of the stabbing. It was reported that their father fainted on hearing of the incident and had to be revived by sympathizers who thronged the house on hearing of the unfortunate incident. Meanwhile, Bauchi State Police Command has arrested the 18-year-old boy for allegedly stabbing his elder brother to death. The arrest was confirmed by State Police Commissioner, Umar Sanda while speaking to Journalists at the NUJ Press Center when he paid a familiarization visit to the leadership of the NUJ. POLL Umar Sanda said that the young man allegedly stabbed his brother after a heated argument over a domestic issue at the games village area of Bauchi metropolis. The Police Commissioner said that full-scale investigation has commenced on the incident after which the young man will be charged to court for prosecution. All efforts to get the father or any close relation to speak on the incident failed as nobody amongst those contacted was ready to talk promising however to speak after the burial of the deceased.